Object oriented programming (OOPs):
    its simply a style of programing. It is one of the most widely used and famous way of creating
    software applications. Other ways of programming are functional programming,Procedural
    is an other example.

Why we should use OOPs?
   OOPs help us to write/manage/change/update easily

There are 4 main pillar off OOPs:
  1)Inheritance
  2)Polymorphism
  3)Abstraction
  4)Encapsulation



What is the class?
    A class is a template/design/idea from which objects are created.

Object:
  Objects are entities with specific values and are used to execute
  the code from classes.

  for interview;
  if else
  loops
  arrays
  string methods